        "release_notes": {
            "en-US": "<ul>      <li>        <b>Important change.</b> The add-on (version from Thunderbid add-on portal) contains now\n        default OAuth credentials, but it still during certification and can handle just limited\n        number of users.\n      </li>      <li>        <b>Breaking change!</b> Use \"desktop app\" oauth client type. Your OAuth credentials requires\n        update. Please follow\n        <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://github.com/kam193/thbrd-signature/wiki/Registering-own-OAuth-app-in-Google\">instructions</a>.\n      </li>      <li>Fix problem with sync stopped shortly after connection.</li>      <li>Show error popup after every 3 failed sync tries.</li>      <li>Show changelog page on major updates.</li>      <li>Dark theme support</li>    </ul>"
        },
        "reviewed": null,
        "url": "https://addons.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/addon/signature-sync-for-gmail/versions/2.0.2",
        "version": "2.0.2"
    },
    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "This extension allows you to automatically use your signature from Gmail accounts in Thunderbird. No longer need to maintain two separated signatures!\n\nYou can select a Gmail account for every Thunderbird account. Signatures are synced on app startup, or when you click a button on the options page. \n\nAfter installing, <b>please visit add-on options page and configure your sync!</b>\n\n100% privacy friendly - nothing is sent outside your Thunderbird, and if you wish, you can configure your own OAuth credentials in Google. This is described on a <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://github.com/kam193/thbrd-signature/wiki/Registering-own-OAuth-app-in-Google\">wiki page</a>. Starting version 2 it's just optional feature."
    },
